Voici une implémentation en Python de l'algorithme de la plus longue sous-séquence commune (PLSC) utilisant la programmation dynamique :

```
def plsc(s1, s2):
    m = len(s1)
    n = len(s2)
    c = [[0] * (n + 1) for _ in range(m + 1)]
    b = [[0] * (n + 1) for _ in range(m + 1)]
    for i in range(1, m + 1):
        for j in range(1, n + 1):
            if s1[i - 1] == s2[j - 1]:
                c[i][j] = c[i - 1][j - 1] + 1
                b[i][j] = "\\"
            elif c[i - 1][j] >= c[i][j - 1]:
                c[i][j] = c[i - 1][j]
                b[i][j] = "|"
            else:
                c[i][j] = c[i][j - 1]
                b[i][j] = "-"
    i, j = m, n
    lsc = ""
    while i > 0 and j > 0:
        if b[i][j] == "\\":
            lsc = s1[i - 1] + lsc
            i -= 1
            j -= 1
        elif b[i][j] == "|":
            i -= 1
        else:
            j -= 1
    return lsc
```

